<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>College Website Project Proposal</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --primary-color: #0f172a;
            --secondary-color: #2563eb;
            --text-color: #334155;
            --bg-color: #f8fafc;
            --card-bg: #ffffff;
            --border-color: #e2e8f0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: var(--text-color);
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 40px;
            background: var(--card-bg);
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1), 0 2px 4px -2px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1);
        }

        header {
            border-bottom: 3px solid var(--secondary-color);
            padding-bottom: 20px;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        h1 {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            margin: 0 0 10px 0;
            font-size: 2.5rem;
        }

        h2 {
            color: var(--primary-color);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding-bottom: 8px;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }

        h3 {
            color: var(--secondary-color);
        }

        .meta-info {
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-color);
            border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }

        .meta-info p {
            margin: 5px 0;
            font-weight: 500;
        }

        ul, ol {
            padding-left: 20px;
        }

        li {
            margin-bottom: 8px;
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        th, td {
            border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            padding: 12px;
            text-align: left;
        }

        th {
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            color: var(--primary-color);
        }

        tr:nth-child(even) {
            background-color: #f8fafc;
        }

        .footer {
            margin-top: 50px;
            padding-top: 20px;
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #64748b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <h1>Project Proposal: Next-Generation College Website</h1>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; color: #64748b; margin: 5px 0 0 0;">A Web Development & Design Initiative</p>
        </header>

        <div class="meta-info">
            <p><strong>Prepared By:</strong> Chauhan Romit</p>
            <p><strong>Role:</strong> Lead Web Developer / Project Proponent</p>
            <p><strong>Target Institution:</strong> Apex University / College Campus</p>
            <p><strong>Date:</strong> July 2026</p>
        </div>

        <section>
            <h2>1. Executive Summary</h2>
            <p>In the digital age, a college website serves as the primary gateway for prospective students, current students, faculty, and alumni. This proposal outlines the development of a modern, responsive, and highly interactive college website. The objective is to replace the current legacy system with a fast, secure, and user-centric platform that streamlines academic administration and boosts institutional branding.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>2. Objectives</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Enhanced User Experience (UX):</strong> Implement an intuitive navigation structure designed for distinct user personas (Students, Faculty, Applicants).</li>
                <li><strong>Mobile Responsiveness:</strong> Ensure 100% seamless functionality across smartphones, tablets, and desktops.</li>
                <li><strong>Centralized Information:</strong> Provide easy access to admissions, courses, examination portals, and campus news.</li>
                <li><strong>Modern Tech Stack:</strong> Utilize robust web technologies to ensure fast loading times and strong security protocols.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>3. Core Website Architecture</h2>
            <p>The proposed website will be divided into the following key modules:</p>
            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Module</th>
                        <th>Key Features</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Public Portal</strong></td>
                        <td>Home Page, About Us, Admissions Info, Course Catalog, Contact Details.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Student Dashboard</strong></td>
                        <td>Attendance tracking, Exam schedules, Fee payment gateway, Assignment submissions.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Faculty Dashboard</strong></td>
                        <td>Syllabus management, Attendance marking, Internal grading system.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Admin Panel</strong></td>
                        <td>User management, Content Management System (CMS) for news, and analytical reports.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>4. Technology Stack (Proposed)</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> HTML5, CSS3 (Tailwind CSS / Bootstrap), JavaScript (React.js)</li>
                <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js / Python (Django)</li>
                <li><strong>Database:</strong> PostgreSQL / MongoDB</li>
                <li><strong>Hosting & Security:</strong> AWS Cloud Hosting, SSL Certification, DDoS protection</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>5. Project Timeline</h2>
            <p>The project is estimated to take <strong>12 weeks</strong> from approval to final deployment:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Weeks 1-2:</strong> Requirements gathering, wireframing, and UI/UX design.</li>
                <li><strong>Weeks 3-6:</strong> Frontend development and core layout structure.</li>
                <li><strong>Weeks 7-9:</strong> Backend integration, database setup, and feature development.</li>
                <li><strong>Weeks 10-11:</strong> Rigorous testing (security, speed, and cross-browser compatibility).</li>
                <li><strong>Week 12:</strong> Final deployment, staff training, and handover.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>6. Conclusion</h2>
            <p>This redesigned website will significantly elevate the institution’s digital presence, improve student engagement, and reduce administrative overhead. I look forward to the opportunity to bring this project to fruition.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="footer">
            <p>&copy; 2026 Chauhan Romit. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
